<subSubSection id="C3196578FF92FFC35CB1FF258AB60D30" pageId="3" pageNumber="116" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BBC36F3FF92FFC35CB1FF258AB60D30" blockId="3.[174,1232,175,266]" pageId="3" pageNumber="116">D i a g n o s i s. This species can be recognized by the mesonotal scutum with three longitudinal rows of stronger setulae on small tubercles (not present in other piophilids), but no presutural supra-alar seta; fore and hind femora mostly black; thoracic spiracle small and slit-like.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
